=Further reading==\n* ''[https://www.waterstones.com/book/the-little-big-beat-book/rory-hoy/9781912587094 The Little Big Beat Book]'' by Rory Hoy, published 10 September 2018, by New Haven Publishing Ltd, {{ISBN|9781912587094}}, pages 48\u201350, outlines Big Bang's involvement in the development of [[Big Beat]] as a musical genre. The book charts the history of Big Beat as a musical genre.<ref>''The Little Big Beat Book'' by Rory Hoy, published 10 September 2018 by New Haven Publishing Ltd: {{ISBN|9781912587094}} - The book outlines the history of [[Big Beat]] as a musical genre and contains 120 interviews with bands and musicians that helped create and produce Big Beat music. Big Bang interview pp 48\u201350: http://www.foyles.co.uk/witem/biography/the-little-big-beat-book,rory-hoy-9781912587094</ref><ref>BBC Radio 6, Craig Charles Radio Show, Craig Charles interviews Rory Hoy, writer of ''the Little Big Beat Book'':https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0000cnr</ref>\n* ''[https://www.waterstones.com/book/the-story-of-big-beat/rory-hoy/9781949515091 The Story of Big Beat: Bookazine]'' by Rory Hoy, published 30 July 2019, by New Haven Publishing Ltd, {{ISBN|978-1949515091}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Music|1980s|UK}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Commons|Big Bang (British Band)}}\n\n[[Category:Alternative dance musical groups]]\n[[Category:Big beat groups]]\n[[Category:Electronic music duos]]\n[[Category:English musical duos]]\n[[Category:English synth-pop groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1988]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from London]]\n[[Category:Nu-disco musicians]]\n", "name_user": "Picachord", "label": "safe", "comment": "adding external link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Big_Bang_(British_band)"}
{"title_page": "Monnow Valley Studio", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n'''Monnow Valley Studio''' is a recording studio in [[Rockfield, Monmouthshire]], Wales.\n\n==History==\nIn the 1970s, Monnow Valley was the rehearsal facility of the famous [[Rockfield Studios]]. It became an independent studio in the 1980s and has been use by many famous bands including [[Oasis (band)|Oasis]], [[Stereophonics]], [[The Charlatans (UK band)|The Charlatans]], [[Manic Street Preachers]], [[Queen (band)|Queen]], [[Black Sabbath]], and [[Iggy Pop]]. \n\n==Clients==\n{{Dynamic list}}\nOver the last thirty years, the studio has been used by many successful artists:\n\n*[[Amplifier]]\n* [[Attack Attack! (UK Band)|Attack Attack!]]\n* [[Devil Sold His Soul]]<ref name=\"these\"/>\n* [[Black Sabbath]]<ref name=\"these\"/>\n* [[Blood Red Shoes]]\n* [[Biffy Clyro]]\n* [[Billy Bragg]]<ref name=\"these\"/>\n* [[Bullet for My Valentine]]\n* [[Casino]]\n* [[Catatonia (band)|Catatonia]]\n* [[The Charlatans (UK band)|The Charlatans]]<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/rock-shrine-goes-sale-690k-2342368|title=Rock shrine goes on sale for #690k|date=4 April 2006|website=walesonline}}</ref>\n* [[The Coral]]\n* [[Deadbeat Darling]]\n* [[Delphic (band)|Delphic]]\n* [[Devin Townsend]]\n* [[The Enemy (UK rock band)|The Enemy]]\n* [[Feeder (band)|Feeder]]\n* [[Fredrika Stahl]]\n* [[Funeral for a Friend]]\n* [[Future of the Left]]\n* [[GLC (rapper)|GLC]]\n* [[Iggy Azalea]]\n* [[Joss Stone]]\n* [[Led Zeppelin]]\n* [[Manic Street Preachers]]<ref name=\"these\"/>\n*[[My Mate Mike]]\n* [[Oceansize]]\n* [[Oasis (band)|Oasis]]<ref>[http://www.oasis-recordinginfo.co.uk/?page_id=588 Oasis at The Pink Museum and Monnow Valley], Oasis Recording info. Retrieved April 2012</ref>\n* [[The Pigeon Detectives]]\n* [[Eugene Francis Jnr]]\n* [[Robert Plant]]\n* [[Iggy Pop]]\n* [[Portishead (band)|Portishead]]\n* [[Pulp (band)|Pulp]]<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n* [[Pretty Violet Stain (band)]]\n* [[Queen (band)|Queen]]\n* [[Rush (band)|Rush]]\n*[[Simple Minds]]\n* [[Stereophonics]]<ref name=\"these\">Tryst Williams, [Bands who have recorded at Monnow Valley Studios include], Western Mail, 2006. Retrieved April 2012</ref>\n* [[Super Furry Animals]]<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n* [[Sylosis]]\n* [[The Stone Roses]]\n* [[The View (band)|The View]]\n* [[Yes! Sir! Boss!]]\n*[[Godsticks]]\n\n==Sources==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|http://www.monnowvalleystudio.com}}\n\n{{coord|51.8359|-2.7517|display=title|region:GB_scale:10000}}\n\n[[Category:Recording studios in Wales]]\n\n\n{{Wales-company-stub}}\n{{recording-studio-stub}}\nOzzy Osbourne\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n'''Monnow Valley Studio''' is a recording studio in [[Rockfield, Monmouthshire]], Wales run by Tom Manning and Megan Manning.\n\n==History==\nIn the 1970s, Monnow Valley was the rehearsal facility of the famous [[Rockfield Studios]]. It became an independent studio in the 1980s and has been use by many famous bands including [[Oasis (band)|Oasis]], [[Stereophonics]], [[The Charlatans (UK band)|The Charlatans]], [[Manic Street Preachers]], [[Queen (band)|Queen]], [[Black Sabbath]], and [[Iggy Pop]]. \n\n==Clients==\n{{Dynamic list}}\nOver the last thirty years, the studio has been used by many successful artists:\n\n*[[Amplifier]]\n* [[Attack Attack! (UK Band)|Attack Attack!]]\n* [[Devil Sold His Soul]]<ref name=\"these\"/>\n* [[Black Sabbath]]<ref name=\"these\"/>\n* [[Blood Red Shoes]]\n* [[Biffy Clyro]]\n* [[Billy Bragg]]<ref name=\"these\"/>\n* [[Bullet for My Valentine]]\n* [[Casino]]\n* [[Catatonia (band)|Catatonia]]\n* [[The Charlatans (UK band)|The Charlatans]]<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/rock-shrine-goes-sale-690k-2342368|title=Rock shrine goes on sale for #690k|date=4 April 2006|website=walesonline}}</ref>\n* [[The Coral]]\n* [[Deadbeat Darling]]\n* [[Delphic (band)|Delphic]]\n* [[Devin 