{"title_page": "Miguel Sapochnik", "text_new": "{{Use British English |date=July 2016 }}\n{{Use dmy dates |date=July 2016 }}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Miguel Sapochnik\n| image              = Miguel Sapochnik by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| image_size         = 220px\n| alt                = \n| caption            = Miguel Sapochnik at [[San Diego Comic-Con International]] in 2016.\n| birth_name         = Miguel Vicente Rosenberg-Sapochnik\n| other_names        = Miguel Rosenberg\n| birth_date         = {{birth year and age|1974|7}}<ref name=\"snowflake\">{{cite web |url=https://www.companieslondon.com/uk/04335462/snowflake-in-hell-films-limited |title=Snowflake in Hell Films Limited |publisher=CompaniesLondon.com |accessdate=2 July 2016 }}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Hammersmith]], [[London]], [[England]]\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = {{Plainlist}}\n* [[Film director]]\n* [[Television director]]\n* [[Storyboard artist]]\n{{Endplainlist}}\n| years_active       = 1996\u2013present\n| spouse             = Alexis Raben (c. 2006)\n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Miguel Sapochnik''' (born '''Miguel Vicente Rosenberg-Sapochnik''') is an English [[film director|film]] and [[television director]] and former [[storyboard artist]]. He is best known as the director of the feature film ''[[Repo Men]]'', and as a director for the [[HBO]] [[epic fantasy]] series ''[[Game of Thrones]]'', for which he won the award for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series|Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series]] at the [[68th Primetime Emmy Awards]] and [[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Drama Series]] at the [[69th Directors Guild of America Awards]].<ref name=\"cinemablend\"/>\n\n==Career==\nSapochnik began his career as a [[storyboard artist]]; some of his credits include ''[[Trainspotting (film)|Trainspotting]]'' (1996, directed by [[Danny Boyle]]) and ''[[The Winter Guest]]'' (1997, actor [[Alan Rickman]]'s directorial debut).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/person/527876/Miguel-Sapochnik/filmography |title=Miguel Sapochnik Filmography |work=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=23 August 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shocktillyoudrop.com/news/14444-exclusive-repo-men-director-miguel-sapochnik |title=Exclusive: ''Repo Men'' director Miguel Sapochnik |work=Shock Till You Drop |date=11 March 2010 |accessdate=23 August 2012 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2000, Sapochnik directed a 2000 short film entitled ''The Dreamer'', which he wrote and directed. He also directed the \"Beautiful Inside\" music video for singer [[Louise Redknapp|Louise]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.variety.com/article/VR1117936124 |title=Sapochnik finally in view |first=Adam |last=Dawtrey |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=15 January 2006 |accessdate=23 August 2012}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2001 and 2005, he was a director of Snowflake in Hell Films Limited.<ref name=\"snowflake\"/>\n\nSapochnik's feature film directorial debut was ''[[Repo Men]]'' (2010), starring [[Jude Law]] and [[Forest Whitaker]].<ref name=\"cinemablend\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/new/Exclusive-Interview-Repo-Men-Director-Miguel-Sapochnik-17650.html |title=Exclusive Interview: Repo Men Director Miguel Sapochnik |last=Rich |first=Katey |work=Cinema Blend |date=19 March 2010 |accessdate=13 April 2012 }}</ref>\n\nSapochnik has worked on American television series, directing episodes of ''[[Awake (TV series)|Awake]]'' (2012), ''[[Fringe (TV series)|Fringe]]'' (2011-12), ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'' (2011-12) and ''[[Mind Games (TV series)|Mind Games]]'' (2014).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/miguel-sapochnik/credits/303421 |title=Miguel Sapochnik Credits |work=[[TV Guide]] |accessdate=23 August 2012}}</ref> \n\nIn 2015, Sapochnik directed two episodes of ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' for the show's [[Game of Thrones (season 5)|fifth season]], \"[[The Gift (Game of Thrones)|The Gift]]\" and \"[[Hardhome]].\" He returned to direct the final two episodes of ''Game of Thrones''{{'}} [[Game of Thrones (season 6)|sixth season]], \"[[Battle of the Bastards]]\" and \"[[The Winds of Winter (Game of Thrones)|The Winds of Winter]]\".<ref>{{cite tweet |user=LovinGoT99 |number=584416131152240640 |author=Watchers on the Wall |date=August 1, 2014 |title=Game of Thrones Season 5: What We Know So Far  |accessdate=6 February 2015 }}</ref>  All of these episodes received acclaim from both critics and viewers. Sapochnik won an Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series at the [[68th Primetime Emmy Awards]], for directing \"Battle of the Bastards\".\n\nIn 2016, Sapochnik directed the series premiere of the show [[Altered Carbon (TV series)|''Altered Carbon'']] for [[Netflix]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/joel-kinnaman-altered-carbon-netflix-1201772819/ |title=Joel Kinnaman to Star in Netflix Sci-Fi Series \u2018Altered Carbon\u2019 |first=Elizabeth |last=Wagmeister |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=May 12, 2016 |accessdate=September 20, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, he directed an episode of [[Iron Fist (TV series)|''Iron Fist'']].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2016/06/game-of-thrones-season-7-directors |title=The Best Director on Game of Thrones Won\u2019t Be Coming Back Next Year |first=Joanna |last=Robinson |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |date=June 29, 2016 |accessdate=September 20, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, he directed the third (\"[[The Long Night (Game of Thrones)|The Long Night]]\") and fifth (\"[[The Bells (Game of Thrones)|The Bells]]\") episodes of the final season of ''Game of Thrones''.<ref name=\"director episodes\">{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/justice-league-interview-fabian-wagner-superman-black-suit/#game-of-thrones|title=\u2018Justice League\u2019 DP Fabian Wagner on Zack Snyder's Cut, Superman's Black Suit & \u2018Game of Thrones\u2019|work=Collider|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|date=December 15, 2017|accessdate=December 18, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171216024149/http://collider.com/justice-league-interview-fabian-wagner-superman-black-suit/#game-of-thrones|archivedate=December 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nSapochnik is of Argentine origin, and has been married to actress Alexis Raben since 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0764601/bio|title=Miguel Sapochnik|website=IMDb|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref>\n\nHe is [[Jewish]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jewishtampa.com/jews-in-the-news/jews-in-the-news-chuck-lorre-dave-franco-and-billy-crystal|title=Jews in the News: Chuck Lorre, Dave Franco and Billy Crystal &#124; Tampa Jewish Federation|website=www.jewishtampa.com}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film credits===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Title !! Notes\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Repo Men]]''\n|\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Bios (film)|BIOS]]''\n|<ref>{{cite web|author1=Brent Lang|author2=Justin Kroll|title=Tom Hanks to Star in Sci-Fi Film \u2018Bios\u2019 From \u2018Game of Thrones\u2019 Director (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/tom-hanks-sci-fi-film-bios-1202599035/|date=26 October 2017|website=Variety|accessdate=23 November 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Television credits===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Show !! Season !! Episode !! Episode title !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | 2011\n| rowspan=3 | ''[[House (TV series)|House]]''\n| rowspan=3 | [[House (season 7)|7]]\n| 9\n| \"[[Larger than Life (House)|Larger Than Life]]\"\n|\n|-\n| 11\n| \"[[Family Practice (House)|Family Practice]]\"\n|\n|-\n| 22\n| \"[[After Hours (House)|After Hours]]\"\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Fringe (TV series)|Fringe]]''\n| [[Fringe (season 4)|4]]\n| 3\n| \"[[Alone in the World (Fringe)|Alone in the World]]\"\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | ''House''\n| rowspan=3 | [[House (season 8)|8]]\n| 7\n| \"[[Dead & Buried (House)|Dead & Buried]]\"\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | 2012\n| 16\n| \"[[Gut Check]]\"\n|\n|-\n| 21\n| \"[[Holding On (House)|Holding On]]\"\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Awake (TV series)|Awake]]''\n| 1\n| 13\n| \"[[Turtles All the Way Down (Awake)|Turtles All the Way Down]]\"\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Falling Skies]]''\n| [[Falling Skies (season 2)|2]]\n| 4\n| \"[[Young Bloods (Falling Skies)|Young Bloods]]\"\n|\n|-\n| ''Fringe''\n| [[Fringe (season 5)|5]]\n| 1\n| \"[[Transilience Thought Unifier Model-11]]\"\n| co-directed with [[Jeannot Szwarc]]\n|-\n| rowspan=4 | 2013\n| ''[[Under the Dome (TV series)|Under the Dome]]''\n| [[Under the Dome (season 1)|1]]\n| 7\n| \"[[Imperfect Circles]]\"\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Revolution (TV series)|Revolution]]''\n| 1\n| 12\n| \"Ghosts\"\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | ''[[Banshee (TV series)|Banshee]]''\n| rowspan=2 | 1\n| 9\n| \"Always the Cowboy\"\n|\n|-\n| 10\n| \"A Mixture of Madness\"\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2014\n| ''[[Mind Games (TV series)|Mind Games]]''\n| 1\n| 1\n| \"Pilot\"\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Extant (TV series)|Extant]]''\n| 1\n| 13\n| \"Ascension\"\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=4 | 2015\n| rowspan=2 | ''[[Game of Thrones]]''\n| rowspan=2 | [[Game of Thrones (season 5)|5]]\n| 7\n| \"[[The Gift (Game of Thrones)|The Gift]]\"\n|\n|-\n| 8\n| \"[[Hardhome]]\"\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Masters of Sex]]''\n| 3\n| 3\n| \"The Excitement of Release\"\n|\n|-\n| ''[[True Detective]]''\n| [[True Detective (season 2)|2]]\n| 5\n| \"Church in Ruins\"\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2016\n| rowspan=2 | ''Game of Thrones''\n| rowspan=2 | [[Game of Thrones (season 6)|6]]\n| 9\n| \"[[Battle of the Bastards]]\"\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series]] <br /> [[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Drama Series]] <br /> Nominated\u2014[[Hugo Award for Best Dramatic Presentation]], Short Form\n|-\n| 10\n| \"[[The Winds of Winter (Game of Thrones)|The Winds of Winter]]\"\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Iron Fist (TV series)|Iron Fist]]''\n| 1\n| 4\n| \"Eight Diagram Dragon Palm\"\n|\n|-\n|2018\n| ''[[Altered Carbon (TV series)|Altered Carbon]]''\n| 1\n| 1\n| \"Out of the Past\"\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |2019\n| rowspan=2 | ''Game of Thrones''\n| rowspan=2 | [[Game of Thrones (season 8)|8]]\n| 3\n| \"[[The Long Night (Game of Thrones)|The Long Night]]\"\n| Nominated\u2014[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series]] <br /> Nominated\u2014[[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Drama Series]]\n|-\n| 5\n| \"[[The Bells (Game of Thrones)|The Bells]]\"\n|\n|-\n|TBA\n| ''[[House of the Dragon]]''\n| 1\n| 1\n| \"TBA\"\n| Also showrunner and executive producer \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Miguel Sapochnik}}\n* {{IMDb name|0764601}}\n\n{{Miguel Sapochnik}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Miguel Sapochnik\n|list =\n{{DirectorsGuildofAmericaOutstandingDirectingDramaSeries}}\n{{EmmyAward DirectingDrama}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sapochnik, Miguel}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:British expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:British film directors]]\n[[Category:British music video directors]]\n[[Category:British television directors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:British storyboard artists]]\n[[Category:People from Hammersmith]]\n[[Category:Primetime Emmy Award winners]]\n[[Category:English people of Argentine descent]]\n[[Category:British Jews]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English |date=July 2016 }}\n{{Use dmy dates |date=July 2016 }}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Miguel Sapochnik\n| image              = Miguel Sapochnik by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| image_size         = 220px\n| alt                = \n| caption            = Miguel Sapochnik at [[San Diego Comic-Con International]] in 2016.\n| birth_name         = Miguel Vicente Rosenberg-Sapochnik\n| other_names        = Miguel Rosenberg\n| birth_date         = {{birth year and age|1974|7}}<ref name=\"snowflake\">{{cite web |url=https://www.companieslondon.com/uk/04335462/snowflake-in-hell-films-limited |title=Snowflake in Hell Films Limited |publisher=CompaniesLondon.com |accessdate=2 July 2016 }}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Hammersmith]], [[London]], [[England]]\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = {{Plainlist}}\n* [[Film director]]\n* [[Television director]]\n* [[Storyboard artist]]\n{{Endplainlist}}\n| years_active       = 1996\u2013present\n| spouse             = Alexis Raben (c. 2006)\n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Miguel Sapochnik''' (born '''Miguel Vicente Rosenberg-Sapochnik''') is an English [[film director|film]] and [[television director]] and former [[storyboard artist]]. He is best known as the director of the feature film ''[[Repo Men]]'', and as a director for the [[HBO]] [[epic fantasy]] series ''[[Game of Thrones]]'', for which he won the award for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series|Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series]] at the [[68th Primetime Emmy Awards]] and [[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Drama Series]] at the [[69th Directors Guild of America Awards]].<ref name=\"cinemablend\"/>\n\n==Career==\nSapochnik began his career as a [[storyboard artist]]; some of his credits include ''[[Trainspotting (film)|Trainspotting]]'' (1996, directed by [[Danny Boyle]]) and ''[[The Winter Guest]]'' (1997, actor [[Alan Rickman]]'s directorial debut).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/person/527876/Miguel-Sapochnik/filmography |title=Miguel Sapochnik Filmography |work=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=23 August 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shocktillyoudrop.com/news/14444-exclusive-repo-men-director-miguel-sapochnik |title=Exclusive: ''Repo Men'' director Miguel Sapochnik |work=Shock Till You Drop |date=11 March 2010 |accessdate=23 August 2012 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2000, Sapochnik directed a 2000 short film entitled ''The Dreamer'', which he wrote and directed. He also directed the \"Beautiful Inside\" music video for singer [[Louise Redknapp|Louise]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.variety.com/article/VR1117936124 |title=Sapochnik finally in view |first=Adam |last=Dawtrey |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=15 January 2006 |accessdate=23 August 2012}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2001 and 2005, he was a director of Snowflake in Hell Films Limited.<ref name=\"snowflake\"/>\n\nSapochnik's feature film directorial debut was ''[[Repo Men]]'' (2010), starring [[Jude Law]] and [[Forest Whitaker]].<ref name=\"cinemablend\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/new/Exclusive-Interview-Repo-Men-Director-Miguel-Sapochnik-17650.html |title=Exclusive Interview: Repo Men Director Miguel Sapochnik |last=Rich |first=Katey |work=Cinema Blend |date=19 March 2010 |accessdate=13 April 2012 }}</ref>\n\nSapochnik has worked on American television series, directing episodes of ''[[Awake (TV series)|Awake]]'' (2012), ''[[Fringe (TV series)|Fringe]]'' (2011-12), ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'' (2011-12) and ''[[Mind Games (TV series)|Mind Games]]'' (2014).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/miguel-sapochnik/credits/303421 |title=Miguel Sapochnik Credits |work=[[TV Guide]] |accessdate=23 August 2012}}</ref> \n\nIn 2015, Sapochnik directed two episodes of ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' for the show's [[Game of Thrones (season 5)|fifth season]], \"[[The Gift (Game of Thrones)|The Gift]]\" and \"[[Hardhome]].\" He returned to direct the final two episodes of ''Game of Thrones''{{'}} [[Game of Thrones (season 6)|sixth season]], \"[[Battle of the Bastards]]\" and \"[[The Winds of Winter (Game of Thrones)|The Winds of Winter]]\".<ref>{{cite tweet |user=LovinGoT99 |number=584416131152240640 |author=Watchers on the Wall |date=August 1, 2014 |title=Game of Thrones Season 5: What We Know So Far  |accessdate=6 February 2015 }}</ref>  All of these episodes received acclaim from both critics and viewers. Sapochnik won an Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series at the [[68th Primetime Emmy Awards]], for directing \"Battle of the Bastards\".\n\nIn 2016, Sapochnik directed the series premiere of the show [[Altered Carbon (TV series)|''Altered Carbon'']] for [[Netflix]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/joel-kinnaman-altered-carbon-netflix-1201772819/ |title=Joel Kinnaman to Star in Netflix Sci-Fi Series \u2018Altered Carbon\u2019 |first=Elizabeth |last=Wagmeister |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=May 12, 2016 |accessdate=September 20, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, he directed an episode of [[Iron Fist (TV series)|''Iron Fist'']].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2016/06/game-of-thrones-season-7-directors |title=The Best Director on Game of Thrones Won\u2019t Be Coming Back Next Year |first=Joanna |last=Robinson |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |date=June 29, 2016 |accessdate=September 20, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, he directed the third (\"[[The Long Night (Game of Thrones)|The Long Night]]\") and fifth (\"[[The Bells (Game of Thrones)|The Bells]]\") episodes of the final season of ''Game of Thrones''.<ref name=\"director episodes\">{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/justice-league-interview-fabian-wagner-superman-black-suit/#game-of-thrones|title=\u2018Justice League\u2019 DP Fabian Wagner on Zack Snyder's Cut, Superman's Black Suit & \u2018Game of Thrones\u2019|work=Collider|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|date=December 15, 2017|accessdate=December 18, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171216024149/http://collider.com/justice-league-interview-fabian-wagner-superman-black-suit/#game-of-thrones|archivedate=December 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nSapochnik is of Argentine origin, and has been married to actress Alexis Raben since 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0764601/bio|title=Miguel Sapochnik|website=IMDb|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref>\n\nHe is [[Jewish]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jewishtampa.com/jews-in-the-news/jews-in-the-news-chuck-lorre-dave-franco-and-billy-crystal|title=Jews in the News: Chuck Lorre, Dave Franco and Billy Crystal &#124; Tampa Jewish Federation|website=www.jewishtampa.com}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film credits===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Title !! Notes\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Repo Men]]''\n|\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Bios (film)|BIOS]]''\n|<ref>{{cite web|author1=Brent Lang|author2=Justin Kroll|title=Tom Hanks to Star in Sci-Fi Film \u2018Bios\u2019 From \u2018Game of Thrones\u2019 Director (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/tom-hanks-sci-fi-film-bios-1202599035/|date=26 October 2017|website=Variety|accessdate=23 November 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Television credits===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Show !! Season !! Episode !! Episode title !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | 2011\n| rowspan=3 | ''[[House (TV series)|House]]''\n| rowspan=3 | [[House (season 7)|7]]\n| 9\n| \"[[Larger than Life (House)|Larger Than Life]]\"\n|\n|-\n| 11\n| \"[[Family Practice (House)|Family Practice]]\"\n|\n|-\n| 22\n| \"[[After Hours (House)|After Hours]]\"\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Fringe (TV series)|Fringe]]''\n| [[Fringe (season 4)|4]]\n| 3\n| \"[[Alone in the World (Fringe)|Alone in the World]]\"\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | ''House''\n| rowspan=3 | [[House (season 8)|8]]\n| 7\n| \"[[Dead & Buried (House)|Dead & Buried]]\"\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | 2012\n| 16\n| \"[[Gut Check]]\"\n|\n|-\n| 21\n| \"[[Holding On (House)|Holding On]]\"\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Awake (TV series)|Awake]]''\n| 1\n| 13\n| \"[[Turtles All the Way Down (Awake)|Turtles All the Way Down]]\"\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Falling Skies]]''\n| [[Falling Skies (season 2)|2]]\n| 4\n| \"[[Young Bloods (Falling Skies)|Young Bloods]]\"\n|\n|-\n| ''Fringe''\n| [[Fringe (season 5)|5]]\n| 1\n| \"[[Transilience Thought Unifier Model-11]]\"\n| co-directed with [[Jeannot Szwarc]]\n|-\n| rowspan=4 | 2013\n| ''[[Under the Dome (TV series)|Under the Dome]]''\n| [[Under the Dome (season 1)|1]]\n| 7\n| \