{"title_page": "Khalilou Fadiga", "text_new": "{{short description|Senegalese footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|           name = Khalilou Fadiga\n|          image =\n|       fullname = Khalilou Fadiga\n|         height = 1.88 m\n|     birth_date = {{birth date and age|1974|12|30|df=yes}}\n|    birth_place = [[Dakar]], Senegal\n|       position = [[Midfielder]]\n|    youthyears1 = 1981\u20131989 |youthclubs1 = Les Enfants de la goutte d'or\n|    youthyears2 = 1989\u20131990 |youthclubs2 = [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]\n|         years1 = 1991\u20131992 |clubs1  = [[Les Enfants de la goutte d'or]]         |caps1  = 0   |goals1  = 0\n|         years2 = 1994\u20131995 |clubs2  = [[R.F.C. de Li\u00e8ge|Royal Li\u00e8ge]]                   |caps2  = 26  |goals2  = 5\n|         years3 = 1995\u20131997 |clubs3  = [[K.V.S.K. United Overpelt-Lommel|Lommel]]        |caps3  = 48  |goals3  = 2\n|         years4 = 1997\u20132001 |clubs4  = [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]]                    |caps4  = 71  |goals4  = 13\n|         years5 = 2000      |clubs5  = \u2192 [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] (loan)                   |caps5  = 21  |goals5  = 1\n|         years6 = 2001\u20132003 |clubs6  = [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]]                            |caps6  = 61  |goals6  = 9\n|         years7 = 2003\u20132004 |clubs7  = [[F.C. Internazionale Milano|Internazionale]]     |caps7  = 0   |goals7  = 0\n|         years8 = 2004\u20132006 |clubs8  = [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]        |caps8  = 13  |goals8  = 1\n|         years9 = 2005      |clubs9  = \u2192 [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] (loan)       |caps9  = 4   |goals9  = 0\n|        years10 = 2007      |clubs10 = [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]]              |caps10 = 6   |goals10 = 0\n|        years11 = 2008      |clubs11 = [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]]                              |caps11 = 17  |goals11 = 0\n|        years12 = 2008      |clubs12 = [[K.F.C. Germinal Beerschot|Germinal Beerschot]]  |caps12 = 10  |goals12 = 0\n|        years13 = 2011      |clubs13 = [[KSV Temse]]                                     |caps13 = 0   |goals13 = 0\n| totalcaps      = 277 |totalgoals = 31\n| nationalyears1 = 2000\u20132008 |nationalteam1 = [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] |nationalcaps1 = 37 |nationalgoals1 = 4\n}}\n\n'''Khalilou Fadiga''' (born 30 December 1974) is a [[Senegal]]ese former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[midfielder]]. He also holds a Belgian passport.\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early career===\nFadiga moved to France when he was six years old. Fadiga began his career at [[Paris Saint-Germain]] in France, but failed to make an impression, and so was transferred to fellow Parisian club, [[Red Star 93]], before moving to Belgian club [[FC Li\u00e8ge]].\n\n===Lommel===\nIt was in Belgium that he found the profile that was to launch his international career. After one season he moved from [[FC Li\u00e8ge]] to Lommel, which is now [[KVSK United]]. He played two seasons at Lommel before he was spotted by [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]].\n\n===Club Brugge===\nFadiga quickly became a fan favorite. He scored nine goals in 67 appearances. In September 2000, the midfielder returned to France when he signed for [[AJ Auxerre]].\n\n===Auxerre===\nIn all, he played in 82 league games for the French club, scoring 10 goals as well as appearing in the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] and [[UEFA Cup]] during season 2002\u201303. In his final season at Auxerre he helped them win the [[2002-03 Coupe de France]], playing in the final as they defeated [[Paris St Germain]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.europe1.fr/sport/psg-auxerre-cetait-deja-il-y-a-12-ans-1339522 |title=PSG-Auxerre, c'\u00e9tait d\u00e9j\u00e0 il y a 12 ans |website=europe1.fr |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Internazionale===\nFadiga moved to [[Internazionale Milano F.C.|Inter Milan]] in the summer of 2003, but the discovery of heart problems did not allow him to feature for the Italian club, apart from appearing in a few friendly games during the Summer. He was released from the [[San Siro (stadium)|San Siro]] side after just one season, but decided against retirement despite the heart problems.\n\n===Bolton Wanderers===\nEnglish club [[Bolton Wanderers FC|Bolton Wanderers]] signed Fadiga for the 2004\u201305 season, after he passed a medical. However, before he made an appearance for Bolton, he collapsed prior to a match in October, and had to be fitted with a [[defibrillator]] due to an irregular heartbeat. Despite stating his desire to return to the game, medical specialists urged him to retire, warning that if during a game his chest was knocked the defibrillator could fail, leading to instant death. However, following a period of rest and passing a medical, Fadiga returned to the Bolton squad in early 2005 and played in five games.\n\nAt the start of the 2005\u201306 campaign Fadiga was loaned to [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] of the [[Football League Championship]], making four appearances. On his return to the [[Reebok Stadium]] he took part in ten games, two of them in the [[UEFA Cup]], before eventually being released in May 2006.\n\n===Coventry City===\nWithout a club at the start of the 2006\u201307 season, he went on trial with [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] and played for their reserve team. He also had trials at [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] and [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] before eventually signing a four-month contract with [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] on 23 February 2007. In April 2007 he suffered a serious Achilles injury in the home game against Preston and it ended his time at Coventry.\n\n===Return to Belgium===\nHe has since been released and returned to his wife's homeland signing with [[AA Gent]]. After one year he moved in June 2008 to [[K.F.C. Germinal Beerschot]], but left Beerschot after short time in December 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.transfermarketweb.com/?action=read&idsel=29226 | title = OFFICIAL, Fadiga quits Germinal Beerschot | accessdate = 24 December 2008 | date = 23 December 2008 | publisher = transfermarketweb.com}}</ref> He signed for [[Belgian Third Division|Third Division]] club [[KSV Temse]] in 2011 before retiring from the game.\n\n==Personal life==\nFadiga is married with a Belgian and has two kids Noah and Naoel. Noah is currently playing for FC Bruges.]\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Senegal's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"NFT\">{{NFT|5823|accessdate=11 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! No !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 7 February 2000 || [[National Stadium, Lagos|National Stadium]], [[Lagos]], Nigeria || {{fb|NGA}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20132 {{aet}} || [[2000 Africa Cup of Nations]]\n|-\n| 2. || 21 July 2001 || [[Sam Nujoma Stadium]], [[Windhoek]], Namibia || {{fb|NAM}} || align=center | '''4'''\u20130 || align=center | 5\u20130 || [[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 CAF Final Round|2002 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 3. || 6 June 2002 || [[Suwon World Cup Stadium]], [[Suwon]], South Korea || {{fb|URU}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 3\u20133 || [[2002 FIFA World Cup Group A|2002 FIFA World Cup]]\n|-\n| 4. || 26 March 2005 || [[Stade L\u00e9opold S\u00e9dar Senghor]], [[Dakar]], Senegal || {{fb|LBR}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 6\u20131 || [[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 CAF Group 1|2006 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{LFP|fadiga-khalilou}}\n\n{{Senegal Squad 2000 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Senegal Squad 2002 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Senegal Squad 2002 World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fadiga, Khalilou}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Cat